  "prompt": "Where do I download Quora for Windows 10?",
  "response": "Quora does not have a standalone desktop application for Windows 10. However, you can access Quora through a web browser by visiting [www.quora.com](https://www.quora.com). Simply open your preferred web browser, such as Chrome, Firefox, Edge, or Safari, and navigate to the Quora website to start using it.\n\nIf you want a more app-like experience on your desktop, you can create a shortcut to Quora on your desktop using your browser:\n\n1. Open your web browser and go to [www.quora.com](https://www.quora.com).\n2. Click on the browser menu (three dots in the upper-right corner for Chrome or Edge).\n3. Look for the option to \"Install Quora\" or \"Create Shortcut\" (wording may vary depending on the browser).\n4. If prompted, choose to open in a window and create the shortcut.\n\nThis will create a shortcut on your desktop that you can use to quickly access Quora.",
